    "actions_taken": [
      "USCG notified Arena of ship contact at 0640 hours on 07-JAN-2021",
      "BSEE notified by USCG at 0700 hours on 07-JAN-2021",
      "BSEE inspector conducted overflight at 0830 and 0900 hours and took photographs",
      "BSEE Accident Investigator coordinated with USCG and NTSB investigators",
      "Arena conducted damage assessment on 07-JAN-2021"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 7, 2021 at approximately 0200 hours, a Chinese Bulk Carrier Cargo ship named 'Ocean Princess' collided with South Pass (SP) 83 A platform owned and operated by Arena Offshore LP. The platform was unmanned and Out of Service (OOS) at the time. Estimated damage cost exceeded $1.5 million. No injuries or pollution occurred. The vessel was drifting in intermittent light to heavy rain when it drifted too close to a safety fairway and ran into the platform while turning. The allision was not found to be caused by a platform-related error.",
